The paper proposes a new technical approach to explain how machine learning models make decisions. This falls under the category of interpretability and explainability of machine learning models, which is a popular research area in computer science. The paper specifically focuses on Bayesian regression mixture models and elastic nets, which are commonly used in machine learning for various tasks such as text mining and image recognition. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision), cs.CL (Computation and Language), and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
